-- TABLE-Albania's trade gap rises 0.1 pct year/year in July
-- 
-- Thu Aug 28, 2014 09:02AM EDT
-- None



TIRANA, Aug 28 (Reuters) - Albania's trade deficit rose 0.1 percent in July compared to the same month last year and fell 10.2 percent over June this year, the Institute of Statistics said on Thursday.

Trade exchanges with countries of the European Union accounted for 86.7 percent of all the trade. Albania's main partners were Italy (37.8 percent), Greece (7.2 percent), China (7.1 percent) and Turkey (5.8 percent), the Institute added. Albania Trade July 2014   June 2014   July 2013 Exports  22,907  22,483  24,288 Imports  47,024  49,349  48,383